        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 2:12AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 210 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fluvanna, or 13 miles southwest of Lake Alan Henry, moving southeast
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Snyder, Fluvanna, J B Thomas Reservoir, Dunn, Randalls Corner, Ira,
Winston Field, and Knapp.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
